x4freetext: The XTU tandem
The Ni targets were 30 mug/cm**2 evaporations on
20 mug/cm**2 carbon foils, enriched to 99.8% and 96.5%
in mass 58 and 64, respectively.
An FeS sample, enriched to around 40% in mass 36, was
used in the sputtering ion source to produce the S-36
beam.
.Optical model FITS.
Three time-of-flight-energy
telescopes consisting of microchannel plates detectors
and 200-300 mm**2 Si surface barrier detectors.
The corrections for the isotopic impurities in the
targets were made.Those corrections were negligible in
the case of Ni-58 and amounted typically to a few per
cent for Ni-64.
.The statistical uncertainties plus a minor
contribution due to the corrections for the isotopical
impurities in the targets. Systematic errors, coming
from poor evaluation of solid angles, were corrected
for by normalizing the elastic yields to the
Rutherford limit at the most forward angles
